**Anyone know where the `Error { ... }` messages are coming from?** I'm having trouble debugging this, but any time I publish anything with Patchbay (and I think [Patchwork too](https://github.com/ssbc/patchbay/issues/252#issuecomment-415725213)) I have something like this printed to my console:

```console
Error {
  key: '%Cb0kLxt0aN5+e2HtLha4C+Y6F4nXEVl6Fd3qhjTP0RQ=.sha256',
  value:
   Error {
     previous: '%L/yat9o2uThz3gOcDLtU05PLYQdusn2U1YTsiPHp3P4=.sha256',
     author: '@+oaWWDs8g73EZFUMfW37R/ULtFEjwKN/DczvdYihjbU=.ed25519',
     sequence: 6622,
     timestamp: 1540599376866,
     hash: 'sha256',
     content:
      '.box',
     signature:
      'j0JZT2jiDmpuHg4bjvZCL141gQBYZbNnTiArVq/dY5zBEnh+32fMLckKV1UCuWO+H100dZqHwDz2g7LLmn5SDw==.sig.ed25519' },
  timestamp: 1540599376891.001 }
```

It's being pretty-printed with color, which makes me think it's intentional, but wrapping each object with "Error" is annoying. My only lead is that I'm getting a similar message on startup, also pretty-printed with color, but I've traced it to levelup:

```
Error { notFound: true, status: 404 }
```

Any ideas on where this might be coming from? I've tried to debug this a half-dozen times but I can't find it.

cc: #javascript #ssbc #patchbay-dev #patchwork-dev #patchcore
